<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Nehemiah on Christian Internet Resources</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/nehemiah/</link><description>Recent content in Nehemiah on Christian Internet Resources</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/nehemiah/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Nehemiah 1</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/nehemiah/chapter-01/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/nehemiah/chapter-01/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="nehemiah-chapter-1">Nehemiah Chapter 1&lt;/h2>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpFirst" align=center style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.25in;text-align:center;'>&lt;b>&lt;span style='font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>1&lt;sup>;1&lt;/sup>&lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The Memoirs of Nehemiah Son of Hacaliah&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="report-from-jerusalem">Report from Jerusalem&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family: "Times New Roman",serif'>In the &lt;b>month Chislev, the twentieth year&lt;/b>, I was in Susa, the capital. &lt;/span>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Hanani, one of my brothers, and some men came from Judah. I asked them about the Jews that had survived the captivity and about Jerusalem. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>They told me, &lt;i>“The remnant in the province is in dire straits and dishonor. The wall around Jerusalem has been torn down and its gates burned.”&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Nehemiah 2</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/nehemiah/chapter-02/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/nehemiah/chapter-02/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="nehemiah-chapter-2">Nehemiah Chapter 2&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="i-was-the-kings-cupbearer">I was the king’s cupbearer.             &lt;/h3>
&lt;p>Neh 1:1-11&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="nehemiah-sent-to-jerusalem">Nehemiah Sent to Jerusalem&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>In the &lt;b>month Nisan, twentieth year of King Artaxerxes&lt;/b>, wine was present, and I took it up to him. I hadn’t been sad in his presence &lt;i>before&lt;/i>. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>So he asked &lt;i>me&lt;/i>, &lt;i>“Why do you look sad, but you’re not sick? This is nothing but sadness in &lt;/i>&lt;i>you.” &lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Nehemiah 3</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/nehemiah/chapter-03/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/nehemiah/chapter-03/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="nehemiah-chapter-3">Nehemiah Chapter 3&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="rebuilding-the-walls">Rebuilding the Walls&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Then Eliashib the high priest with his relatives the priests built the Sheep Gate. They consecrated it and hung its doors and consecrated the wall to the Tower of a Hundred and the Tower of Hananel. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Next to him men from Jericho built, and &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family: "Times New Roman",serif'>next to them Zaccur son of Imri.&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Nehemiah 4</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/nehemiah/chapter-04/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/nehemiah/chapter-04/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="nehemiah-chapter-4">Nehemiah Chapter 4&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="opposition-to-the-work">Opposition to the Work&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpFirst" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>When Sanballat heard we were rebuilding the wall, he was furious and ridiculed the Jews. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>In front of his relatives and wealthy men in Samaria, he asked, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“What are these feeble Jews doing? Are they going to restore it for themselves? Can they offer sacrifices? Can they finish it in a day? Can they remake something out of the charred stones from dusty rubble?”&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> &lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Nehemiah 5</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/nehemiah/chapter-05/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/nehemiah/chapter-05/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="nehemiah-chapter-5">Nehemiah Chapter 5&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="nehemiah-stops-the-oppression-of-the-poor">Nehemiah Stops the Oppression of the Poor&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpFirst" style='margin-bottom:0in;'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            &lt;/span>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>There was a loud outcry by husbands and wives against their fellow Jews. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Some were saying, &lt;i>“There are a lot of us along with our sons and daughters. We need more food to survive.” &lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Others said, &lt;i>“We’re mortgaging our fields, vineyards, and houses for grain because of the famine.”&lt;/i> &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Yet
&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>others were saying, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Nehemiah 6</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/nehemiah/chapter-06/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/nehemiah/chapter-06/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="nehemiah-chapter-6">Nehemiah Chapter 6&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="conspiracy-against-nehemiah">Conspiracy Against Nehemiah&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Sanballat, Tobiah, Geshem the Arab, and the rest of our enemies found out I’d rebuilt the wall so there wasn’t any break in it—although I hadn’t set up the doors in the gates yet. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Sanballat and Geshem sent me a message&lt;i>, “Meet us at Chephirim in the Plain of Ono.” &lt;/i>They were planning to harm me. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>I sent messengers, &lt;i>“I’m in an extensive project. Why should the work stop while I’m with you?” &lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>They sent me four messages like that; I answered them the same way. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v5" id="v5">&lt;sup class="verse-num">5&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Then Sanballat sent his servant a fifth time with an open letter in hand. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v6" id="v6">&lt;sup class="verse-num">6&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>He’d written, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Nehemiah 7</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/nehemiah/chapter-07/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/nehemiah/chapter-07/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="nehemiah-chapter-7">Nehemiah Chapter 7&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="the-walls-are-finished">The Walls Are Finished&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The wall had been rebuilt, and I’d set up the doors and appointed gatekeepers, singers, and Levites. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>I put Hanani my brother—along with Hananiah commander of the fortress—in charge of Jerusalem &lt;a name="_Hlk146040578">because he was a reliable man that respected God more than most. &lt;/a>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>I told them, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“Don’t open the gates till the sun is hot. While they’re standing guard, shut and bolt the doors. Appoint guards from the people that live inside Jerusalem, each at his post by his own house.” &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> &lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Nehemiah 8</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/nehemiah/chapter-08/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/nehemiah/chapter-08/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="nehemiah-chapter-8">Nehemiah Chapter 8&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="ezra-reads-the-law">Ezra Reads the Law&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The people congregated in the square by the Water Gate, and asked Ezra to bring &lt;i>The Book of the Law of Moses &lt;/i>the L&lt;/span>&lt;span style='font-size:9.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family: "Times New Roman",serif'>ORD&lt;/span>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height: 115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> had given Israel. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>On the &lt;b>first day,&lt;/b> &lt;b>seventh month&lt;/b>, he brought it to the assembly of men and women—anybody that could understand. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>He read from early morning till noon, and the people listened. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>He stood on a wooden podium built for that purpose. Beside him stood Pedaiah, Mishael, Malchijah, Hashum, Hash-baddanah, Zechariah, and Meshullam on his left; and Mattithiah, Shema, Anaiah, Uriah, Hilkiah, and Maaseiah on his right.
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v5" id="v5">&lt;sup class="verse-num">5&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>He unrolled the scroll where everybody could see &lt;i>it&lt;/i>, because he was standing above them. When he unrolled it, they stood up. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v6" id="v6">&lt;sup class="verse-num">6&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>He blessed the L&lt;/span>&lt;span style='font-size:9.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family: "Times New Roman",serif'>ORD&lt;/span>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height: 115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> the great God, and the people answered, &lt;i>“Amen!&lt;/i> &lt;i>Amen!”&lt;/i> and raised their hands. Then they bowed low in worship with their faces toward the ground. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v7" id="v7">&lt;sup class="verse-num">7&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Jeshua, Bani, Sherebiah, Jamin, Akkub, Shabbethai, Hodiah, Maaseiah, Kelita, Azariah, Jozabad, Hanan, Pelaiah, and the Levites explained the Law while they stood in their places. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v8" id="v8">&lt;sup class="verse-num">8&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>As they read the Law, they translated &lt;i>it&lt;/i> so the people could understand it.&lt;b>       &lt;/b>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Nehemiah 9</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/nehemiah/chapter-09/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/nehemiah/chapter-09/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="nehemiah-chapter-9">Nehemiah Chapter 9&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="the-people-confess-their-sin">The People Confess Their Sin&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>On the &lt;b>twenty-fourth of that month&lt;/b>, the Israelites gathered with fasting in burlap and doused with dust. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>They separated from foreigners and confessed their and their ancestors’ sins. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>While they stood in their place, they read from the Law for a fourth of the day. For another fourth they confessed and worshiped the L&lt;/span>&lt;span style='font-size: 9.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>ORD&lt;/span>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> their God. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>On the Levites’ platform stood &lt;b>Jeshua, Bani, Kadmiel, Shebaniah,&lt;/b> Bunni, &lt;b>Sherebiah,&lt;/b> Bani, &lt;i>and &lt;/i>Chenani, and appealed to the L&lt;/span>&lt;span style='font-size: 9.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>ORD&lt;/span>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> their God.&lt;b>                                                                     &lt;/b>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Nehemiah 10</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/nehemiah/chapter-10/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/nehemiah/chapter-10/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="nehemiah-chapter-10">Nehemiah Chapter 10&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="people-that-sealed-the-covenant">People That Sealed the Covenant&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1-8&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The sealed document showed the names of these &lt;u>priests&lt;/u>: Nehemiah the governor, son of Hacaliah; Zedekiah, Seraiah, Azariah, Jeremiah, Pashhur, Amariah, Malchijah, Hattush, Shebaniah, Malluch, Harim, Meremoth, Obadiah, Daniel, Ginnethon, Baruch, Meshullam, Abijah, Mijamin, Maaziah, Bilgai, and Shemaiah; &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v9" id="v9">&lt;sup class="verse-num">9&lt;/sup> &lt;u>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>the Levites&lt;/span>&lt;/u>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family: "Times New Roman",serif'>: Jeshua son of Azaniah, Binnui of the family of Henadad, Kadmiel; &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v10" id="v10">&lt;sup class="verse-num">10&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>and their brothers Shebanaih, Hodiah, Kelita, Pelaiah, Hanan, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v11" id="v11">&lt;sup class="verse-num">11&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Mica, Rehob, Hashabiah, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v12" id="v12">&lt;sup class="verse-num">12&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Zaccur, Sherebiah, Shebaniah, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v13" id="v13">&lt;sup class="verse-num">13&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Hodiah, Bani, Beninu;&lt;/span>&lt;b>&lt;sup>&lt;span style='font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%; font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> &lt;/span>&lt;/sup>&lt;/b>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Nehemiah 11</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/nehemiah/chapter-11/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/nehemiah/chapter-11/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="nehemiah-chapter-11">Nehemiah Chapter 11&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="the-leaders-in-jerusalem">The Leaders in Jerusalem&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;a name="_Hlk124880892">&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;/a>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The people’s leaders &lt;i>already &lt;/i>lived in Jerusalem, but the rest of the people cast lots to bring one in ten to live in Jerusalem, the holy city, while nine-tenths stayed in the other towns. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The people commended those who volunteered to move to Jerusalem.&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>These are the leaders of the province who lived in Jerusalem, but in the towns of Judah each lived on his own property: the Israelites, priests, Levites, Temple servants, and descendants of Solomon’s servants. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Some of the people of Judah and Benjamin lived in Jerusalem. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Nehemiah 12</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/nehemiah/chapter-12/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/nehemiah/chapter-12/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="nehemiah-chapter-12">Nehemiah Chapter 12&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="priests-and-levites">Priests and Levites&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>These are the priests and Levites that came up with Zerubbabel &lt;i>the king, &lt;/i>son of Shealtiel, and Jeshua &lt;i>the high priest&lt;/i>: Seraiah, Jeremiah, Ezra, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Amariah, Malluch, Hattush, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Shecaniah, Rehum, Meremoth, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Iddo, Ginnethoi, Abijah, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v5" id="v5">&lt;sup class="verse-num">5&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Mijamin, Maadiah, Bilgah, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v6" id="v6">&lt;sup class="verse-num">6&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Shemaiah and Joiarib, Jedaiah, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v7" id="v7">&lt;sup class="verse-num">7&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Sallu, Amok, Hilkiah, and Jedaiah. These were the leaders of the &lt;u>priests&lt;/u> and their relatives at the time of Jeshua.&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Nehemiah 13</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/nehemiah/chapter-13/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/nehemiah/chapter-13/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="nehemiah-chapter-13">Nehemiah Chapter 13&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="nehemiahs-final-reforms">Nehemiah’s Final Reforms&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:.45pt; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>That day they read out loud from the &lt;i>Book of Moses&lt;/i> so the people could hear it. There they found that no Ammonite or Moabite should ever enter God’s assembly. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>That was &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>because they didn’t provide the Israelites with bread and water, but hired Balaam to curse them. But our God turned the curse into a blessing. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>When they heard the Law, they excluded all foreigners from Israel. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>